statement:
Write the matrix $A$ so that the equation

\begin{align*}s \left[\begin{array}{c} 1 \\ 2 \end{array} \right] + t \left[\begin{array}{c} 3 \\ -1 \end{array} \right] = \left[\begin{array}{c} -2 \\ 10 \end{array} \right]\end{align*}
can be represented as a matrix equation,

: A\textbackslash{}left{[}\textbackslash{}begin\{array\}\{c\} s
\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{} t \textbackslash{}end\{array\}
\textbackslash{}right{]} =
\textbackslash{}left{[}\textbackslash{}begin\{array\}\{c\} -2
\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{} 10 \textbackslash{}end\{array\}
\textbackslash{}right{]}.

sols:
Following the hint gives us

\begin{align*}
\left[\begin{array}{cc}
a & b \\ c & d
\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{c} s\\t \end{array}\right] &= \left[\begin{array}{c} as+bt \\ cs+dt \end{array}\right] = s\left[\begin{array}{c} a \\ c\end{array}\right] + t\left[\begin{array}{c} b \\ d\end{array}\right]\end{align*} Comparing to the original equation gives

\begin{align*}A = \left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 & 3 \\ 2 & -1
\end{array}\right]\end{align*}

hints:
Set

\begin{align*}A = \left[\begin{array}{cc}
a & b \\ c & d
\end{array}\right]\end{align*} and calculate

\begin{align*}\left[\begin{array}{cc}
a & b \\ c & d
\end{array}\right] \left[\begin{array}{c} s\\t \end{array}\right]\end{align*}
Matching one-by-one will give you the values of \emph{a}, \emph{b},
\emph{c} and \emph{d}.
